display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {Cat}^{\to }]]></fr:tex>. After redrawing a few general results in that context, we show that fibrations over a given base are pseudo-coalgebras for a 2-comonad on  <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathbf {Cat}}_{/B}]]></fr:tex>. We use that result to explain how an arbitrary fibration is equivalent to one with a splitting.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>